      "span_text": "Bertrand Russell, quoted from, succinctly and aptly summarized this when, in New Hopes for a Changing World, he remarked \"One of the painful things about our time is that those who feel certainty are stupid, and those with any imagination and understanding are filled with doubt and indecision\"."
